introduction 1 on 4 april 2008, i delivered judgment dismissing the application made by mr and mrs lowe for damages in respect of the loss which they had allegedly suffered as a result of their acquisition of a mack prime mover.
if so, they claimed damages for breach of implied contractual conditions as to fitness for purpose and merchantability, relying on s 71 of the trade practices act 1974 (cth) ("the tpa"): see lowe v mack trucks australia pty ltd [2008] fca 439 (" lowe v mack trucks ").